        level: 2,
        body: 'Monthly active users, customer acquisition cost, and net revenue retention are standard fintech KPIs. They are useful in US and European markets where financial products operate on similar infrastructure, regulatory environments, and user behaviour patterns. In African fintech, these metrics require significant contextualisation to be meaningful. An African mobile money platform that counts "monthly active users" as anyone who made a single P2P transfer may have an MAU figure that overstates genuine product engagement by 3x compared to a platform counting users who engaged with financial management or credit features. Customer acquisition cost in agent-network-based financial services includes agent commission structures, mobile airtime costs, and physical infrastructure that do not appear in CAC calculations for app-based fintechs. Know which definition of each KPI your business is using and whether it maps to actual revenue-generating behaviour.'
